OL,3,CJoint mayor would 'discriminate'
OL,4,Cagainst Cornish people, says Labour MP
OL,6,FDorset, Somerset and Wiltshire have
OL,7,Fsubmitted plans for a "Wessex"
OL,8,Fauthority, while it's thought North
OL,9,FSomerset may attempt to join the
OL,10,Falready-existing West of England
OL,11,FCombined Authority.
OL,13,FIt all sounds quite complicated, but
OL,14,Fit effectively means that elected
OL,15,Fmayors will be given greater control
OL,16,Fof their local areas and, in theory,
OL,17,Fthings should get done quickly and
OL,18,Fsuccessfully.
OL,20,FHowever, in Devon and Cornwall, it's
OL,21,Fnot that straightforward.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/10
